%N A173841 Number of permutations of 1..n with no adjacent pair summing to n+1.
%C A173841 If a(n,k) is the number of permutations of 1..n with no adjacent pair summing to n+k, then a(n,k) = a(n,k+1) for n+k even. [proved by William Keith]
%F A173841 k = 1; a(n,k) = Sum_{j=0..m} (-2)^j*binomial(m,j)*(n-j)! where m = max(0, floor((n-k+1)/2)). [From _Max Alekseyev_, on the Sequence Fans Mailing List]
%F A173841 a(2n) = A007060(n); a(2n-1) = A285850(n)/(2n). - _David Radcliffe_, Sep 09 2025
